Weg is a modern CLI for managing Frappe development environments.

It provides fast, declarative configuration for Frappe apps and benches,
with support for multiple Frappe versions and databases.

Quick start:
  weg new myapp          Create a new Frappe app
  weg init               Initialize weg in existing project
  weg start              Start development servers
  weg sync               Apply configuration changes

Learn more at https://github.com/gavindsouza/weg

Usage:
  weg [command]

Getting Started:
  create      Create a new Frappe bench with Devbox
  init        Initialize weg in a directory
  new         Create a new Frappe app
  run         Clone and run a Frappe app instantly
  scaffold    Scaffold development tooling into your project

Daily Development:
  build       Build assets and frontend
  doctor      Check environment health
  log         View and manage logs
  restart     Restart development services
  start       Start development services
  status      Show the current state of the weg environment
  stop        Stop development services
  sync        Synchronize environment with configuration
  test        Run tests for the current app

Site & Data:
  api         Make API calls to Frappe sites
  cache       Manage Frappe cache
  db          Database operations
  doc         Document operations
  doctype     DocType operations
  exec        Run a command in the bench context
  fixtures    Manage data fixtures
  py          Run Python with frappe context pre-loaded
  scheduler   Manage the background job scheduler
  site        Manage Frappe sites
  user        User management

Apps:
  add         Add an app to the project
  app         Manage Frappe apps
  remove      Remove an app from the project
  update      Update apps to latest versions
  upgrade     Upgrade Frappe to next version

Deployment:
  bench       Run bench commands
  cloud       Frappe Cloud operations
  docker      Docker Compose operations
  image       Build and manage container images
  remote      Work with remote Frappe sites

Weg Itself:
  config      View and modify weg configuration
  convert     Convert between app-centric and bench-centric modes
  mcp         MCP server for AI assistant integration
  self        Manage weg itself and its dependencies
  version     Show version information
  workspace   Manage expanded code workspace

Additional Commands:
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  help        Help about any command

Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
  -h, --help                      help for weg
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
      --version                   version for weg
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg [command] --help" for more information about a command.
